Durban - Former Durban Chamber of Commerce and Industry chief executive Dumile Cele is part of a new organisation that wants to tackle Durban’s problems.
City Story is a network of individuals from different spheres of life who want to empower each other to bring about a powerful collaboration to spark remarkable change in the city. 

The group is made up of NPOs, business people, religious groups, academia, eThekwini municipality and government. Cele said the group came about three years ago. 
“It’s basically a group of us who are passionate about seeing Durban become everything it can be. We want to propel Durban forward by way of up-scale and impact,” Cele said. 


 







